               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; names of the donor and the scribe; a few lines in the incipit page, alternating with black lines; two initial lines of each section of the text; names of Hebrew letters in Ps. 118 (e.g., fols. 28vb, 30rb, 31va); elements of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numbers; some other words, e.g., wä-yǝblu (e.g., fols. 17va, 18rb, 19ra), halle (fols. 24va, 25rb), wä-ʾǝmzǝ (e.g., fols. 30va, 31rb, 32va), wä-kaʿǝbä (fols. 35ra, 57va), qǝdmä wängel (e.g., fols. 68vb, 67vb, 65va), dǝḫrä wangle (e.g., fols. 69ra, 65vb, 79ra).</rubric>
                     <incipit>
